  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Bug Report\r\n\r\n**Deviation from expected behavior:**\r\nThe rook operator is only creating the `rook-ceph-csi` secret during cluster creation, and not during an upgrade to v1.1.X.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\nThe rook operator should create the `rook-ceph-csi` secret during an upgrade such that the CSI driver works out of the box.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (minimal and precise):**\r\n<!-- Please let us know any circumstances for reproduction of your bug. -->\r\nUpgrade any rook-ceph cluster to 1.1.0 from a previous 1.0.x version, then try to create a CSI provisioned storage class and PVC.  \r\n\r\nView the csi-provisioner logs for the appropriate provisioner, you'll see the missing secret in the errors: \r\n\r\n```\r\nfailed to provision volume with StorageClass \"test\": error getting secret rook-ceph-csi in namespace rook-ceph: secrets \"rook-ceph-csi\" not found\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n* OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release): Centos 7\r\n* Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`): 3.10.0-957.27.2.el7.x86_64\r\n* Cloud provider or hardware configuration: on-prem\r\n* Rook version (use `rook version` inside of a Rook Pod): v1.1.0\r\n* Storage backend version (e.g. for ceph do `ceph -v`): ceph version 13.2.6 (7b695f835b03642f85998b2ae7b6dd093d9fbce4) mimic (stable)\r\n* Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.15.3\r\n* Kubernetes cluster type (e.g. Tectonic, GKE, OpenShift): baremetal (kubeadm)\r\n* Storage backend status (e.g. for Ceph use `ceph health` in the [Rook Ceph toolbox](https://rook.io/docs/rook/master/ceph-toolbox.html)): HEALTH_OK\r\n",
